Good call. Don’t touch registration yet.

First freeze the current working server state, then compare:
	•	server repo
	•	GitHub remote
	•	your Mac local repo

Do it in this order.

1) On the server: capture exactly what is running

Run on the Ubuntu server:

cd /opt/monetchat/app
echo "BRANCH:" && git branch --show-current
echo "COMMIT:" && git rev-parse HEAD
echo "REMOTE:" && git remote -v
echo "STATUS:" && git status --short

Then check diff against HEAD:

cd /opt/monetchat/app
git diff --stat

Then check if .env or secrets are tracked:

cd /opt/monetchat/app
git status --short
git ls-files .env env 2>/dev/null

2) On the server: create a clean branch for the running server state

Since this server state is the one that works, preserve it first.

cd /opt/monetchat/app
git checkout -B server

Now stage everything except secrets:

cd /opt/monetchat/app
git add -A
git restore --staged .env env 2>/dev/null || true
git status --short

If you see .env or env still staged somehow, unstage them before commit.

Then commit:

cd /opt/monetchat/app
git commit -m "Server working state: deploy fixes, Prisma workaround, Ollama integration"

If it says nothing to commit, that is okay. It means server files already match git.

3) On the server: compare with remote before push

cd /opt/monetchat/app
git fetch origin
echo "LOCAL server branch:"
git rev-parse HEAD
echo "REMOTE server branch:"
git rev-parse origin/server 2>/dev/null || echo "origin/server does not exist"
echo "COMMITS only on local:"
git log --oneline origin/server..HEAD 2>/dev/null || true
echo "COMMITS only on remote:"
git log --oneline HEAD..origin/server 2>/dev/null || true

If you want to overwrite any existing remote server branch with this working state, do:

cd /opt/monetchat/app
git push -u origin server --force

That makes GitHub’s server branch match the actual working server.

4) On your Mac: cross-check local vs remote before pulling

In your local repo on Mac:

cd /path/to/your/local/monetchat
git remote -v
git fetch origin
git branch --show-current
git status --short

Then compare local branch with remote branches:

cd /path/to/your/local/monetchat
echo "LOCAL HEAD:" && git rev-parse HEAD
echo "REMOTE server:" && git rev-parse origin/server
echo "REMOTE main/current branch:" && git rev-parse origin/$(git branch --show-current 2>/dev/null) 2>/dev/null || true

See what differs:

cd /path/to/your/local/monetchat
git log --oneline HEAD..origin/server
git log --oneline origin/server..HEAD

5) On your Mac: pull the exact working server state safely

If you want your laptop to match the server exactly:

cd /path/to/your/local/monetchat
git checkout -B server origin/server

If you already have uncommitted local work, stash first:

cd /path/to/your/local/monetchat
git stash push -u -m "before-sync-with-server"
git checkout -B server origin/server

6) Final verification on Mac

cd /path/to/your/local/monetchat
git branch --show-current
git rev-parse HEAD
git status --short

That should now match origin/server.

